CFC Stanbic Shares Jump Most in Week on Appointment Report

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-07-07T12:34:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/cfc-stanbic-jumps-most-in-three-weeks-on-appointment-report.html
CFC Stanbic Holdings Ltd. (CFCB) , the Kenyan
unit of Standard Bank Group Ltd., gained the most in almost a
week after  Business Daily  reported it hired a former World Bank
official to head its equity-research desk in Nairobi.  CFC shares jumped 1 percent to 51 shillings as of the end
of trading at 3 p.m. local time, the biggest gain since July 1.  The company hired Marcel Mballa-Ekobena, Business Daily
said. Mballa-Ekobena was previously portfolio officer at the
International Finance Corp., where he was in charge of private-
equity investments in  Latin America , the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
